# Almirant Platform Instructions (injected by runner — DO NOT EDIT)

## Skills

You have access to Almirant platform skills. Use `/skill-name` to invoke them.
Available skills: implement, validate, document, fix, runner-implement,
runner-document, ideate, create-tasks, nightly-fix, pr, dod-review.

## MCP Server

The `almirant` MCP server is configured and provides tools for managing
work items, boards, sprints, documents, and project data.

## Conventions

- Use `bun` as package manager (never npm/yarn/pnpm)
- Follow existing project conventions and patterns
- Run type-check and lint before committing
- Commit with format: `type(TASK-ID): description`
- Push after each task completion

## Fundamental Principles

1. Read files completely before modifying
2. Consult library docs with context7 or web before implementing
3. Never make dummy implementations — implement real functionality
4. Apply SOLID principles in every implementation
5. Do not generate junk files — delete test files after verifying unless explicitly asked to keep them
6. No classes in frontend — use functional programming (pure functions, custom hooks, functional components)
7. No refactoring without explicit instruction
8. Incremental implementation — small, testable steps
9. Always include error handling

## Restrictions

- **NO classes** in frontend (no class UserEntity, no class UserService, no extends React.Component)
- **NO unnecessary files** (especially *.md documentation)
- **NO dummy implementations** — always real functionality
- **NO large refactors** without explicit approval
- Always use composition over inheritance
- Always use factory functions or direct initialization instead of constructors
